<br>
It's like they use the proper wording for the weapon but not the effect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulimpylionbait.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LimpyLionBait</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#333333>(9/30/02 7:18:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=738.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MS4 - Can they be equiped with armors and weapons?</span><hr size=1> I zoned into Griegs the other day, to escape some irritable  revenants and bloodtribes, and played around with MSII for a bit.<br>
<br>
You can summon pets of any player race! That was fun to have a troll pet or a halfling pet. I even made a doppelganger of me :P  You can give them weapons, which show up visually, but they do not visually show the phantom plate - whether this means they do not equip it I dont know. <br>
<br>
I was hoping to make a gnome pet with full red plate and 2 swords, but alas that was not meant to be..<br>
<br>
Soloing in Griegs so far:  Grieg and friends: 2  Me: 0<br>
Darn you Dark Sendings!<br>
<br>
Limpy<br>
